":"Norton, Worcestershire, Anglie","Hampshire, England":"Hampshire, Anglie"},"da":{"about 1286–after 4 February 1330":"omkring 1286–efter 4. februar 1330","1270–1318":"1270–1318","1310–1344":"1310–1344","1286–1330":"1286–1330","1330":"1330","1286":"1286","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","after 4 February 1330":"efter 4. februar 1330","1315":"1315","1344":"1344","1310":"1310","about 1310":"omkring 1310","about 1286":"omkring 1286","1318":"1318","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Southwick, Hampshire, England":"Southwick, Hampshire, England","Petersfield, Hampshire, England":"Petersfield, Hampshire, England","Norton, Worcestershire, England":"Norton, Worcestershire, England","Hampshire, England":"Hampshire, England"},"nl":{"about 1286–after 4 February 1330":"circa 1286–na 4 februari 1330","1270–1318":"1270–1318","1310–1344":"1310–1344","1286–1330":"1286–1330","1330":"1330","1286":"1286","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","after 4 February 1330":"na 4 februari 1330","1315":"1315","1344":"1344","1310":"1310","about 1310":"circa 1310","about 1286":"circa 1286","1318":"1318","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Southwick, Hampshire, England":"Southwick, Hampshire, England","Petersfield, Hampshire, England":"Petersfield, Hampshire, England","Norton, Worcestershire, England":"Norton, Worcestershire, England","Hampshire, England":"Hampshire, England"},"en":{"about 1286–after 4 February 1330":"about 1286–after 4 February 1330","1270–1318":"1270–1318","1310–1344":"1310–1344","1286–1330":"1286–1330","1330":"1330","1286":"1286","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","after 4 February 1330":"after 4 February 1330","1315":"1315","1344":"1344","1310":"1310","about 1310":"about 1310","about 1286":"about 1286","1318":"1318","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Southwick, Hampshire, England":"Southwick, Hampshire, England","Petersfield, Hampshire, England":"Petersfield, Hampshire, England","Norton, Worcestershire, England":"Norton, Worcestershire, England","Hampshire, England":"Hampshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Norton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of the many places so called, from Old English <i>north</i> ‘north’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘enclosure, settlement’. In some cases it is a variant of   Norrington  .","Irish: altered form of   Naughton  , assimilated to the English name (see 1 above).","Jewish (American): adoption of the English surname (see 1 above) in place of some similar (like-sounding) original Ashkenazic surname."],"variants":[{"name":"Norrington","meanings":["English:","(southeastern): from Norringtonend in Redbourn (Hertforshire), Northingtown Farm in Grimley (Worcestershire), or Norrington in Alvediston (Wiltshire). All three names are from Old English <i>north in tūne</i> ‘to the north of the village’.","possibly a variant of <b>Northampton</b>, a habitational name from the city of this name, which was named with Old English <i>north</i> ‘north’ + <i>hām</i> + <i>tūn</i> ‘homestead, home farm’."]}]},{"name":"Jacob","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical name, from Hebrew <i>Yaakov</i>. This was borne by perhaps the most important of all the patriarchs in the Book of Genesis. Jacob was the father of twelve sons, who gave their names to the twelve tribes of Israel. He was the son of Isaac and Rebecca and twin brother of Esau. According to the story in Genesis, he was the cunning younger twin, who persuaded his brother Esau to part with his right to his inheritance in exchange for a bowl of soup (‘a mess of pottage’). Later, he tricked his blind and dying father into blessing him in place of Esau. The derivation of the name has been much discussed. It is traditionally explained as being derived from Hebrew <i>akev</i> ‘heel’ and to have meant ‘heel grabber’, because when Jacob was born ‘his hand took hold of Esau's heel’ (Genesis 25:26). This is interpreted later in the Bible as ‘supplanter’ Esau himself remarks, ‘Is he not rightly named Jacob? for he has supplanted me these two times’ (Genesis 27:36). <i>Jacob</i> is especially common as a Jewish given name, although it also became very popular among the Puritans from the 16th century onwards, and has again been widely used since the 1990s.  Compare  James ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":4,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":29,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":42,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Jacob de Norton was born about 1286, in Southwick, Hampshire, England. He had at least 1 daughter with Elizabeth de la Stane. He died after 4 February 1330, in Norton, Worcestershire, England."},"et":{"about 1286–after 4 February 1330":"umbes 1286–pärast 4. veebruari 1330","1270–1318":"1270–1318","1310–1344":"1310–1344","1286–1330":"1286–1330","1330":"1330","1286":"1286","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","after 4 February 1330":"pärast 4. veebruari 1330","1315":"1315","1344":"1344","1310":"1310","about 1310":"umbes 1310","about 1286":"umbes 1286","1318":"1318","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Southwick, Hampshire, England":"Southwick, Hampshire, England","Petersfield, Hampshire, England":"Petersfield, Hampshire, England","Norton, Worcestershire, England":"Norton, Worcestershire, England","Hampshire, England":"Hampshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1286–after 4 February 1330":"noin 1286–4. helmikuuta 1330 jälkeen","1270–1318":"1270–1318","1310–1344":"1310–1344","1286–1330":"1286–1330","1330":"1330","1286":"1286","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","after 4 February 1330":"4. helmikuuta 1330 jälkeen","1315":"1315","1344":"1344","1310":"1310","about 1310":"noin 1310","about 1286":"noin 1286","1318":"1318","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Southwick, Hampshire, England":"Southwick, Hampshire, England","Petersfield, Hampshire, England":"Petersfield, Hampshire, England","Norton, Worcestershire, England":"Norton, Worcestershire, England","Hampshire, England":"Hampshire, England"},"fr":{"about 1286–after 4 February 1330":"environ 1286–après 4 février 1330","1270–1318":"1270–1318","1310–1344":"1310–1344","1286–1330":"1286–1330","1330":"1330","1286":"1286","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","after 4 February 1330":"après 4 février 1330","1315":"1315","1344":"1344","1310":"1310","about 1310":"environ 1310","about 1286":"environ 1286","1318":"1318","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Southwick, Hampshire, England":"Southwick, Hampshire, Angleterre","Petersfield, Hampshire,